msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_useful_items.md:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This robe has cloth patches of various shapes and colors covering it. While "
"wearing the robe, you can use an action to detach one of the patches, "
"causing it to become the object or creature it represents. Once the last "
"patch is removed, the robe becomes an ordinary garment.    \n"
"The robe has two of each of the following patches:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_useful_items.md:16
msgid "Dagger"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_useful_items.md:16
msgid "Bullseye lantern (filled and lit)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_useful_items.md:16
msgid "Steel mirror"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_useful_items.md:16
msgid "10-foot pole"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_useful_items.md:16
msgid "Hempen rope (50 feet, coiled)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_useful_items.md:16
msgid "Sack"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: sources/gamemaster_rules/magic_items/robe_of_useful_items.md:18
msgid ""
"In addition, the robe has 4d4 other patches. The GM chooses the patches or "
"determines them randomly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
